anel_heading_mw_bba4cfb1-ead1-4fea-a862-19ad4d32542a" class=3D"panel-collap=
se collapse"><div class=3D"panel-body">
            <p>Input volume, specified as an
                <em class=3D"varname">m</em>-by-<em class=3D"varname">n</em=
>-by-<em class=3D"varname">p</em>-by-<em class=3D"varname">c</em>
              numeric array. For grayscale volumes, <code class=3D"argument=
">c</code> is 1. For RGB volumes,
                <em class=3D"varname">c</em> is 3. RGB volumes can only be =
of class
              <code class=3D"literal">uint8</code>, <code class=3D"literal"=
>uint16</code>, <code class=3D"literal">single</code>, and
                <code class=3D"literal">double</code>. </p>
          <p class=3D"datatypelist"><strong>Data Types: </strong><code item=
